title: 111-year-old grandma defies heat, boycott calls to cast ballot

description: Congress MP Rahul Gandhi and Samajwadi Party chief Akhilesh Yadav have urged voters to opt for the INDIA bloc instead of the NDA, emphasizing that the 2024 Lok Sabha elections will determine the future trajectory of the nation. At their first joint rally, held in Amroha on Saturday, they accused BJP of attempting to alter the Constitution, which they claimed went "against the very basic spirit of India".
title: Caste census, no Agnipath: Rahul Gandhi-Tipu pitch in 1st rally

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman criticized AIMIM chief Asaduddin Owaisi on Saturday following the circulation of a viral video showing him meeting and commending a beef shop owner in Hyderabad. During his Lok Sabha election campaigning in Hyderabad, Owaisi passed through a beef shop, met the owner and praised him. “Rehan beef shop zindabad. Kaise ho bhai? Salaam alaikum.
title: Owaisi’s ‘keep butchering’ pat for beef shop owner irks FM Sitharaman

description: Many are well-versed in Formula 1, but shift to Formula 9, showcased by the Naveen Patnaik-led Biju Janata Dal (BJD) in unveiling its candidates for the upcoming state assembly elections. Beginning with its debut list revealed on March 27 (2+7=9), which comprised 72 (7+2=9) candidates, the party has adhered to this numerical pattern in its subsequent releases. Even the initial list of Lok Sabha candidates, announced on the same date, featured nine names.
title: BJD banks on 'Formula 9' for success

description: High drama erupted in BSP as the nomination form of their candidate, Chhotelal Gangwar from the Bareilly constituency, got rejected on Saturday due to some blank columns. Meanwhile, chaos ensued in the Aonla seat, with Abid Ali and Satveer Singh both submitting their nomination forms under the BSP symbol, each asserting to be the party's "official choice."
title: DM junks BSP Bareilly pick, Maya sign ‘forged’ in Aonla
Woman, daughter clear class X boards together

description: A dispute erupted between the LG’s office and AAP regarding the controversy surrounding chief minister Arvind Kejriwal’s insulin levels while in jail. Despite his pending application requesting insulin administration and consultation with his personal physician before a Delhi court, which had instructed the ED and Tihar Jail authorities to respond by Saturday, with a ruling anticipated on Monday, the LG V K Saxena’s office disclosed a medical report from the jail submitted to him on Friday.
title: Delhi LG & AAP in bitter row over Kejriwal’s sugar levels
Thief who posed as judge, gave many ‘bail’, dies

description: TMC has disrupted the INDIA alliance's efforts to unveil a unified manifesto for the opposition bloc, aimed at projecting a coherent sense of purpose in the upcoming Lok Sabha elections. Reliable sources indicate ongoing attempts to persuade TMC chief and West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee to cooperate, emphasizing the critical need to promptly publish a basic consensus document outlining the opposition's pledges to voters. Banerjee's resistance is identified as the primary obstacle hindering its release.
title: INDIA alliance tries to convince TMC for joint manifesto

description: Tesla CEO Elon Musk has deferred his trip to India due to pressing work obligations, assuring that he will reschedule it later this year. Originally planned to coincide with a meeting with Prime Minister Modi, Musk intended to unveil substantial investments, spanning billions of dollars, particularly in the realm of a pioneering electric car initiative for Tesla and the satellite communication endeavor Starlink. Musk, who recently teased his visit via a post on his X handle, conveyed the update on the same platform.
title: Elon Musk defers visit to India; Congress says ‘writing on the wall’

description: One day after senior NCP politician Chhagan Bhujbal withdrew from the Nashik Lok Sabha race, the All-India Mahatma Phule Samata Parishad asserted that members of the OBC community are disappointed that Bhujbal, who also serves as the outfit's national president, was not chosen as the Nashik LS candidate by Mahayuti partners.
title: Mahayuti ignores Chhagan Bhujbal for Nashik seat, upsets OBCs

description: During an election rally endorsing BJP's Mathura candidate Hema Malini in Vrindavan on Saturday, Union Home Minister Amit Shah asserted that the "Congress and SP" had been "completely eliminated in the first phase" in Uttar Pradesh. "In 2017, two princes had come together... They have come together in 2024 as well, (but) BJP will win maximum seats in the state," Shah said.
title: Congress-SP wiped out in UP in first phase of LS polls: Amit Shah
Chhattisgarh's Gadchiroli may break polling record, cross 72%
Avoid contact with lawyers: Madras HC to subordinate judges
5,000 red-eared slider baby turtles seized at Chennai airport
Can’t be held without trial indefinitely: Court in Kapoor case
17 Kanker dead, were shot in cold blood, claim Maoists
HDFC Bank net profit rises 37 per cent to 16,511 crore

description: Indian exporters are facing challenges as costs surge due to Houthi attacks on shipping in the Red Sea, resulting in a significant rise in cargo insurance premiums. Some products have seen increase as high as 500%, while the average insurance premium is now 60% higher. Reasons for increase is heightened risks in the region, prompting insurers to raise premiums for vessel insurance..
title: Exporters suffer as Houthi attacks make vessel cover costlier
Congress' dig at ‘outgoing’ PM as Elon Musk defers India trip
Odisha boat capsize toll rises to 8, cops arrest 2

description: The visual rebranding of Doordarshan's news channels, characterized by a shift in the color of its logo from red to orange, has stirred controversy. West Bengal CM Mamata Banerjee and the Minister of Information and Broadcasting engaged in a heated exchange over what the opposition labeled as an effort to "saffronize" the national broadcaster.
title: Doordarshan's 'saffron' logo sparks political slugfest
Three Jain couples to follow their kids into monkhood tomorrow

description: In February, the Employees Provident Fund Organisation (EPFO), responsible for retirement funds, saw an increase of 1.55 million net members, with nearly 780,000 being new additions, according to recently released data. An important observation from the data is the prominence of the 18-25 age bracket, comprising a substantial 56.4% of the total new members in February. This suggests that the bulk of those entering the organized workforce are young individuals, mostly first-time job seekers, as stated in an official announcement.
title: EPFO added 7.8L new members in Feb, 56% aged 18-25 years
Ex-babu, son picked up by ED after SC quashes liquor scam FIR
Online radio, streaming apps help young Sindhis tune in to culture

description: The Enforcement Directorate carried out synchronized searches in Mumbai, Chennai, Kolkata, and Delhi as part of an investigation into the illegal online forex trading case involving the octafx.com website and mobile app. OctaFx India Pvt Ltd, OctaFx and their associated entities have been accused of cheating investors under the guise of forex trading, thereby earning a profit, ED said.
title: Illegal forex trading: ED freezes Rs 2.7 crore in bank accounts

description: Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud gave enthusiastic approval to the new criminal laws scheduled for enforcement starting July 1, stating on Thursday, "These laws signify a watershed moment for our society because no law affects the day-to-day conduct of our society like the criminal law." CJI said BNSS encompassed a holistic approach to deal with crimes in the digital age.
title: CJI: New criminal laws put our legal framework into new age

description: The Congress in Karnataka is under pressure as the opposition BJP intensified its focus on law and order, highlighting it as a key election concern. This comes in the wake of allegations of "love jihad" following the tragic stabbing of 24-year-old MCA student Neha Hiremath in Hubballi on Thursday, as well as the devastating killing of four members of the Bakale family in Gadag early Friday.
title: Girl's murder turns law & order into major poll issue

description: Another explosive start by Travis Head set up Sunrisers Hyderabad to crush Delhi Capitals by 67 runs in the IPL on Saturday. Head and Abhishek Sharma combined for 125 without loss in the first six overs — the highest score in an IPL powerplay — and Sharma was out two balls later for 46 off 12 balls. The openers made 131 in a mere 38 balls. Head continued his onslaught to 89 off 32 until he was caught at long on in the ninth over at 154-3. The visitors finished at 266-7, their third 250-plus total this season, and bowled out Delhi for 199 in 19.1 overs at Arun Jaitley Stadium.
title: 'Never want your head down': Gavaskar consoles Pant

description: The US House has passed a bill that demands TikTok be banned in the United States unless its Chinese proprietor divests ownership within a year. House Republicans made TikTok part of a larger foreign aid package, a key agenda item for President Joe Biden, garnering broad congressional backing particularly for nations like Ukraine and Israel. This maneuver fast-tracked the banning process after the bill initially stalled in the Senate.
title: US House passes bill to ban TikTok, aid to Israel, Ukraine, Taiwan
Maldives' Sunday polls a test of Muizzu's India policy too

description: Travis Head's spectacular 89 propels Sunrisers Hyderabad to a commanding 266/7 against Delhi Capitals, resulting in a resounding 67-run victory against Delhi Capitals at Arun Jaitley Stadium. Head blasted a 16-ball 50 in an explosive opening stand with Abhishek Sharma to tear into the opposition attack as Hyderabad reached 100 in five overs and 125 in six. Hyderabad jumped to second spot behind Rajasthan Royals with five wins in seven matches.
title: Travis Head powers SRH to victory against Delhi Capitals

description: Facing a daunting target of 267 runs, Delhi Capitals initially seemed in contention thanks to blistering innings from Jake Fraser-McGurk (65 off 18 balls) and Abishek Porel (42 off 22 balls). However, once both batsmen were dismissed, Delhi's chase lost momentum as Sunrisers Hyderabad's bowlers struck at crucial intervals, mounting pressure on the opposition.
title: 'We played catch up ...': Pant pinpoints what led to DC's crushing loss

description: Bollywood actor Pankaj Tripathi faced tragedy when his sister Sarita Tiwari and brother-in-law Rajesh Tiwari, known as Munna Tiwari, were in a fatal road accident near GT Road in Nirsa. Sadly, Rajesh lost his life, while Sarita sustained severe injuries and is receiving treatment. Rajesh, an Indian Railways employee stationed in Chittaranjan, was returning there from their village in Bihar. Pankaj had previously lost his father in August 2023.
title: Pankaj Tripathi's brother-in-law passes away in road accident: Report
2 Japanese navy helicopters carrying 8 crew believed crashed in Pacific
US House votes to ban TikTok if it doesn't cut ties to China

description: Mahavir Jayanti, celebrating Lord Mahavir's birth, emphasizes non-violence, truthfulness, self-discipline, and compassion. The festival includes fasting, ceremony of abhishek, blood donation camps, and distributing food to the needy, with people exchanging best wishes and messages. Here are the best wishes, messages, quotes and images to share with your family and friends on this auspicious occasion of Mahavir Jayanti:
title: Happy Mahavir Jayanti 2024: Best wishes, messages, quotes

description: The collapse of the Rambagh crematorium wall in Madanpuri claimed five lives, including Tanya, Khushboo, Manoj Gaba, Devidayal alias Pappu, and Krishna Kumar alias Baba DJ. Avtar Singh highlighted the poor construction of the wall.
title: Crematorium wall collapses in Gurgaon, 5 dead including 2 young girls

description: Ever since Hardik Pandya replaced a highly successful Rohit Sharma -- a five-time title winner -- as skipper at Mumbai Indians, the 30-year-old has been subjected to constant on-field booing by the spectators and social media ridicule. In the first 7 matches this season, Hardik has 141 runs to his name at an average of 23.50 with no half-centuries. On the bowling front, Hardik has bagged a mere 4 wickets and has leaked runs at an economy rate of 11 RPO.
title: 'Hardik struggling with mental health issues due to IPL booing'

description: Jake Fraser-McGurk's explosive innings showcased his prowess and batting acumen as he reached the milestone in a whirlwind fashion, leaving spectators in awe of his talent. His blistering fifty came in a mere 15 deliveries, underlining his ability to accelerate the scoring rate and dismantle opposition bowlers with ease. Chasing a mammoth 267 against Sunrisers Hyderabad, Fraser-McGurk finally perished after a scintillating 18-ball 65 runs knock which included five fours and seven thunderous sixes.
title: Fraser-McGurk slams fastest fifty for DC, joint third-fastest in IPL history

description: The Election Commission has declared fresh polls at 11 polling stations in the I-Inner Manipur parliamentary constituency. The voting is scheduled for April 22. In the initial phase on April 19, incidents of intimidation and firing were reported at two locations in Inner Manipur. In Thamnapokpi under Moirang in Bishnupur district, armed individuals discharged multiple rounds near a polling booth, causing voters to flee.
title: EC announces fresh polls on 11 Manipur polling stations
Wall of a crematorium in Gurugram collapsed, 4 dead
4 bogies of goods train derailed at Ayodhya Dham Junction railway station

description: Smashing the hapless Delhi Capitals bowlers left, right and centre, Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma provided a vertical take-off to Sunrisers in a dazzling display of power-hitting. With both batters going all guns blazing, Sunrisers raised the fastest ever team hundred -- in just 5 overs -- in the history of IPL. Along with that the duo added 125 runs in powerplay -- the highest-ever score in T20 cricket's history ever.
title: 'Ye theek nahi ho raha': SRH carnage sets internet ablaze

description: YS Sharmila declared assets worth Rs 132.56 crore for the Kadapa parliament seat, with significant borrowings from brother Jagan and sister-in-law Bharathi. Her husband Anil Kumar also disclosed substantial assets and liabilities.
title: Sharmila owes Jagan & wife over 100 crore, reveals affidavit

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad opener Abhishek Sharma continued his power-hitting in the Indian Premier League 2024, smashing six sixes against Delhi Capitals. Sharma, along with Australian Travis Head, led Sunrisers Hyderabad to the highest powerplay score in T20 cricket history, amassing 125 runs in the first six overs. His performance raised hopes of claiming the title of IPL's fastest fifty.
title: How Abhishek almost broke this big IPL record

description: PM Modi on Saturday slammed the Congress government for mismanaging Bengaluru's infrastructure problems. He highlighted the severe water crisis in parts of Bengaluru, leading to water rationing and penalties for excessive water usage. Modi accused the Congress government of turning the tech hub into a city dependent on water tankers controlled by a mafia.
title: 'Tech city to tanker city': PM attacks Cong over B'luru's water crisis

description: 'Unbelievable fun, sheer entertainment, vertical take-off,' said an elated Sunil Gavaskar on-air as Sunrisers Hyderabad openers went on a batting rampage against Delhi Capitals in the national capital on Saturday. SRH opener Travis Head and Abhishek Sharma made a mockery of the DC bowlers as they went in sixth gear from the word go in a destructive and never-seen-before power-hitting display.
title: Bowlers' massacre! SRH create powerplay world record

description: Nasa's Bill Nelson raises concerns about China concealing military space activities as civilian. US-China space race intensifies. Tiangong vs ISS contrasted. China-Moon lead concerns. Lunar ambitions detailed. Tianhe module, global collaboration, scientific research, Mars missions highlighted.
title: Nasa chief: China is hiding military presence in space

description: Mumbai Police has announced gangster Lawrence Bishnoi and his brother Anmol Bishnoi as wanted accused in connection to the shooting outside Salman Khan's residence in Bandra. Additional sections, including 506 (2), 115, and 201, have been added to the FIR. Two suspects have been apprehended from Bhuj for firing outside Salman Khan's Galaxy Apartments on April 14.
title: Lawrence Bishnoi declared wanted in firing at Salman's house case

description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal had stopped taking insulin months before his arrest and is on a basic anti-diabetes oral medicine, officials said on Saturday, citing a report by the Tihar jail administration to Lt Governor VK Saxena. In response, AAP leader Atishi said the report has "exposed" the BJP's "conspiracy".
title: 'Kejriwal stopped taking insulin months before his arrest'

description: Nasa utilizes AI and open science to address climate change challenges through technological advancement, transparency, data sharing, global collaboration, and educational outreach, setting a precedent for effective environmental stewardship and scientific inquiry.
title: How Nasa plans to use AI to combat climate change

description: Elon Musk criticizes Israel's strike on Iran's Isfahan Airbase, emphasizing the paradox of US funds attacking American F-14 Tomcats. He advocates for a peaceful approach to global conflicts, suggesting technology be utilized for space exploration instead of warfare.
title: 'Our tax dollars': Elon Musk on irony of US and Israel-Iran conflict

description: Former Russian President Dmitry Medvedev suspects Western involvement in an alleged assassination plot against Ukrainian President Zelenskyy, following the arrest of Pawel K in Poland for collaborating with Russian intelligence.
title: Medvedev suggests West may be behind alleged plot to assassinate Zelenskyy

description: A WZ-7 Soaring Dragon drone of the Chinese People's Liberation Army was spotted flying in close proximity to the Philippines, ahead of preparations by the Southeast Asian country to receive the delivery of Indian BrahMos supersonic cruise missiles, The Eurasian Times reported. According to the report, the distinctive joined-wing shape of the WZ-7 drone caught the attention of Raffy Tima, a correspondent for Philippine news organisation GMA News, as it traversed the skies over the West Philippine Sea, an area within the South China Sea to the northwest of the Philippines.
title: Chinese military drone spotted flying close to the Philippines ahead of BrahMos delivery

description: In the dynamic realm of entertainment, today's highlights include Rajkummar Rao's openness about undergoing chin fillers, Shilpa Shetty's involvement in a money laundering case, Priyanka Chopra and Nick Jonas' return to their renovated LA home, updates on Salman Khan's 'Bajrangi Bhaijaan 2' script, and anticipation surrounding 'Kalki 2898 AD''s new release date announcement.
title: TOP 5 entertainment news of the day
'Paida toh bahut kar diye …': Nitish takes a swipe at Lalu over 'too many kids'

description: Making a triumphant return to the international arena after leading a prolonged protest against former WFI chief Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh, celebrated Indian wrestler Vinesh Phogat secured a Paris Olympics quota in the women's 50kg category at the Asian Olympic Qualifier in Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan on Saturday. Joining her in booking their tickets to Paris were Anshu Malik (57kg) and U23 world champion Reetika (76kg), who both reached the tournament final with impressive performances.
title: Vinesh secures 50kg Paris Olympics quota for India

description: The 29-year-old wrestler has now secured her third consecutive Olympic quota, having previously represented India in the Rio Games (2016) and Tokyo (2020). Despite facing challenges, Vinesh showcased her strength and experience throughout the tournament, swiftly defeating her opponents. This achievement marks India's second quota place for the Paris Games, following Antim Panghal's bronze medal-winning performance in the 53kg category at the World Championships last year.
title: Vinesh secures 50kg Paris Olympics quota for India

description: West Bengal Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee on Saturday alleged that the Election Commission of India chalked out seven-phase polls to enable Prime Minister Narendra Modi and his cabinet colleagues to carry out extensive campaigning using the nation's resources. Addressing a public meeting at Gajol in Malda district in support of Maldaha Uttar TMC candidate Prasun Banerjee, a former IPS officer, Mamata Banerjee, the party supremo, said polls have been scheduled from April 19 to June 1 so that Modi and his cabinet colleagues can travel on special planes across the country before every phase to "overwhelm the Opposition".
title: EC chalked out seven-phase polls to assist BJP campaigning: Mamata

description: Former Pakistan skipper Shahid Afridi commended Rohit Sharma for his exemplary representation of India. He emphasised the crucial role that sports play in promoting improved ties between India and Pakistan. Afridi reflected on previous cricket tours involving the two countries, implying that such occasions contributed to the development of more robust connections.
title: Afridi welcomes Rohit's proposal on Indo-Pak series resumption

description: David J. Bier's study shows a growing trend of H-1B workers changing jobs. Cyrus D. Mehta provides insights into H-1B transfer processes, fees, and key considerations for employers and workers navigating job shifts within the program.
title: Explained: How more H-1B visa holders are switching jobs

description: Virat Kohli prioritizes passion over struggles, discussing this in a viral video with Gaurav Kapoor. He reflects on the contrast between cricket challenges and real-life hardships, emphasizing his love for the game. Virat says while looking at his past and where he has reached now, he cannot use words like struggle and sacrifice when it comes to the hard work he has done over the years to become this successful.
title: I cannot use words like struggle and sacrifice: Virat Kohli

description: Indian student in US died from 'Blue Whale Challenge'. Over 130 deaths globally. Players manipulated into escalating dares over 50 days. 'Curator' selects victims via social media, using cyberbullying and blackmail.
title: What is Blue Whale Challenge, game linked to Indian student’s death

description: Veteran wicketkeeper-batter Dinesh Karthik, who has been in phenomenal form in this IPL, has not given up on his dream to play for India again and would do "everything he can to be in that flight" to the T20 World Cup in the USA and West Indies next month.
title: Karthik: '100 per cent ready to play T20 World Cup'

description: KKR mentor Gautam Gambhir and star RCB batter Virat Kohli  found a moment of connection, discussing the nuances of cricketing rivalry and camaraderie on the eve of Kolkata Knight Riders vs Royal Challengers Bengaluru match in Kolkata on Saturday. With mutual respect as their guiding principle, they explored the essence of sportsmanship and the responsibilities of leadership.
title: Watch: Viral video of Kohli, Gambhir's animated chat
FIR lodged against DK Shivakumar for violation of MCC

description: Union Home Minister Amit Shah criticized the Congress party, suggesting that if they had won the 2019 Lok Sabha polls, Kota might have turned into a base for the Popular Front of India (PFI). Shah highlighted BJP's achievements post-2014 and 2019 elections, citing the abrogation of Article 370, construction of the Ram Temple, enactment of the Citizenship Amendment Act (CAA), and the introduction of women's reservation in legislative bodies.
title: 'Kota would have become PFI house if...': Shah slams Congress

description: Bitcoin undergoes a process known as "halving," which gradually reduces the rate at which new bitcoins are generated, thereby limiting the overall supply. This method has systematically decreased the mining reward over time, aligning with the creator Satoshi Nakamoto's vision to cap the total number of bitcoins at 21 million.
title: Bitcoin's latest 'halving' has arrived: What you need to know
Emirates restores regular flights to and from flood-hit Dubai

description: Former India cricketer Gambhir Gambhir also reminisced about the unwavering support he received from team owner Shah Rukh Khan during his rough patch in 2014. Shah Rukh assured him, "You won't be dropping yourself as long as you're here," reinforcing his confidence in Gambhir's abilities. It served him as a motivation to do well and win the title in 2014.
title: Gambhir reveals KKR's mantra, says it's not the most...

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi on Saturday said the Congress has accepted its defeat even before the Lok Sabha poll results are out, and took a swipe at Rahul Gandhi, saying that just as he lost from Amethi in 2019, the "Congress' sahabzade" will lose the Wayanad parliamentary seat this time.
title: 'After Amethi, Rahul Gandhi will have to leave Wayanad as well': PM

description: Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah critiques JD(S)-BJP alliance, citing anti-incumbency against Modi. Questions BJP's governance, accuses JD(S) of communalism. Emphasizes Congress support without 'Modi wave'. Discusses Neha Hiremath's tragic murder and subsequent arrest, condemning political exploitation.
title: Modi govt facing strong anti-incumbency, claims K'taka CM Siddaramaiah
Priyanka dismisses PM's claim on voters rejecting Cong in phase 1 polls

description: Women account for only 8.6% of the 1,198 candidates running for 87 parliamentary seats in Phase 2, which begins on April 26. This is somewhat more than the 8.2% representation of women candidates in the 102 Lok Sabha constituencies that voted on Friday.
title: LS polls: Women candidates make up 8.6% of total in Phase 2

description: Despite Maoist boycott, residents in Bastar Lok Sabha voted. Puvarti, a Maoist stronghold, abstained. Low turnout due to fear. Konta saw 54.31% turnout. Security camps address challenges in areas like Puvarti.
title: Why people stay away from voting in village of dreaded Maoist leader
HDFC Bank Q4 results: Net profit increases to Rs 16,511 crore

description: A former Congress MLA from Madhya Pradesh's Shivpuri district and a group of local party leaders have switched sides to join the BJP, causing a member of the Congress to label them as "betrayers." In the lead-up to the Lok Sabha elections, the BJP had initiated a drive to bring dissatisfied Congress members into its ranks in Madhya Pradesh.
title: 'Betrayers': Congress after over 100 leaders cross over to BJP in MP

description: In his attempt to catch Ravindra Jadeja's aerial hit near the long-on fence, Hooda could only tip the ball over the bar, causing it to land beyond the boundary ropes for a six. Despite this outcome, LSG fielding coach Jonty Rhodes interpreted it as a commendable effort, noting that it effectively halted Dhoni from coming to the crease as the next batsman.
title: Watch: LSG's Hooda awarded for keeping Dhoni away for five balls

description: Doordarshan faced criticism for changing logo colour to orange, with concerns over saffronisation. The new logo was unveiled by DD News on X, sparking online backlash and political discussions. Jawhar Sircar, a Rajya Sabha member from TMC and former CEO of Prasar Bharati (DD, AIR), expressed his concern over what he perceives as the "saffronisation" of the national broadcaster.
title: DD's decision to change logo colour to saffron draws criticism
Russia says 50 Ukrainian drones shot down
‘Very heavy obligations’: Musk cancels much-anticipated India visit
Zomato gets Rs 11.82 crore tax demand notice

description: AAP alleges conspiracy against Arvind Kejriwal in Tihar jail, denying insulin. Delhi health minister highlights multiple organ damage conspiracy. Enforcement Directorate accuses Kejriwal of high sugar intake. Senior advocate Abhishek Singhvi mentions medical bail and hospital shift.
title: Arvind Kejriwal being pushed towards 'slow death', claims AAP

description: Royal Challengers Bangalore wicketkeeper-batter Dinesh Karthik once again showed why he is recognized as one of the world's top finishers. Karthik powered through with an explosive 83 off 35 balls as RCB scored 262 runs while chasing a target of 287 against Sunrisers Hyderabad. Although his efforts did not result in a win for RCB, his exceptional finishing skills have reignited conversations about his potential selection for India's T20 World Cup squad, which will be announced soon.
title: Can Karthik's finishing skills fetch him T20 WC ticket?

description: Modi criticizes Sonia's move to Rajya Sabha from Lok Sabha, predicts Rahul losing in Wayanad. Congress lacks confidence in Lok Sabha elections, reflecting a shift in leadership dynamics.
title: 'No courage to ...': PM Modi's Rajya Sabha dig at Sonia Gandhi

description: Hailing the enactment of the new criminal justice laws as a watershed moment for society, Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud on Saturday said India is set for a significant overhaul of its criminal justice system. Speaking at a conference here on 'India's Progressive Path in the Administration of Criminal Justice System', he said the new laws would be successful if those, who are in charge of implementing them, adapt to them.
title: New criminal justice laws signify watershed moment for our society: CJI

description: Weather forecasters knew days in advance that a major storm was heading for the United Arab Emirates and authorities issued warnings asking citizens to stay home. Yet its largest city Dubai was still brought to a halt this week, with one of the worst rain events in decades flooding streets, homes and highways.
title: Dubai floods expose weaknesses to a rapidly changing climate

description: Mumbai Indians' batsman Tim David and batting coach Kieron Pollard have been fined 20% of respective match fees for breaching IPL's Code of Conduct during Mumbai Indians vs Punjab Kings match. Both admitted to the offence and accepted the match referee's sanction. The controversy revolved around taking DRS for a wide delivery.
title: IPL: Caught providing illegal help, MI's Pollard & David fined

description: HRA claims mismatch: Taxpayers should remain cautious. If there's a discrepancy between the rent paid and the rent received by the landlord, potential tax evasion issues may arise. Taxpayers making false HRA claims, whether intentionally or unintentionally, should be concerned about receiving a tax evasion notice from the income tax department.
title: HRA claims and tax scrutiny: Here's what experts suggest taxpayers should do

description: Gautam Gambhir is known for his stern demeanor both on and off the field. Whether he's playing cricket, traveling, attending events, in the dugout, or speaking to players, Gambhir maintains a serious expression and seldom smiles. In a video shared by the Kolkata Knight Riders, host Cyrus Broacha playfully remarked to Gambhir during the Knights Dugout Podcast that he has a lovely smile.
title: 'Yeh toh meri wife ne...': Gambhir after being told he has 'lovely' smile

description: Murder of Neha Hiremath led to Congress-BJP clash in Karnataka over 'love jihad' accusation. Arrest of suspect Fayaz Khondunaik. Protests by ABVP. Minister criticizes law and order. Govt denies 'love jihad'. CM cites personal reasons for the tragedy.
title: Karnataka: BJP, Congress spar over student’s murder

description: Rahul Gandhi accuses PM Modi of running a 'school of corruption'. BJP leaders take a 'crash course' covering 'Entire Corruption Science'. The course includes a 'scathing attack' on Rahul moving from Amethi to Wayanad.
title: PM Modi running 'school of corruption' in country: Rahul Gandhi

description: Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud expresses appreciation for the enactment of new criminal justice laws, highlighting the importance of India undergoing a significant overhaul of its criminal justice system.
title: India set for significant overhaul of criminal justice system: CJI

description: Indian commercial banks are considering using iris scans for transaction verification, especially for senior citizens, due to reliability issues with fingerprints and thumb impressions. Discussions are ongoing with the Reserve Bank of India and other stakeholders regarding implementation challenges and cybersecurity concerns.
title: Iris scan for senior citizens soon? Banks look at options

description: IIT-K experiments with cloud seeding using various chemicals to induce rainfall and clear pollutants. Testing in regions like Maharashtra, Karnataka, and Andhra Pradesh shows potential for addressing water scarcity through artificial rain technology.
title: IIT Kanpur tests artificial rain: What it is and now it works

description: Imran Khan accuses jail authorities of poisoning Bushra Bibi's food, deteriorating her health. Requests tests at Shifa International Hospital. Bushra Bibi files petition alleging contaminated food and psychological torture in sub-jail.
title: Imran claims his wife was given food laced with 'toilet cleaner'

description: Former Mumbai Indians fast bowler Mitchell McClenaghan asserts that Lucknow Super Giants captain KL Rahul has always been a strong candidate for a place in India's 15-player squad for the upcoming T20 World Cup, scheduled to begin on June 1 in the USA and the West Indies. KL Rahul returned to cricket after experiencing right quadriceps pain during India's defeat in the first Test against England earlier this year.
title: Ex-MI star makes big comment on KL Rahul's T20 WC future

description: An Australian newspaper revealed that 23 Chinese swimmers competed in the Tokyo Olympics despite doping suspicions. The swimmers tested positive for trimetazidine, but Chinese authorities blamed contamination. The World Anti-Doping Agency and World Aquatics accepted this, refraining from sanctions. WADA's Olivier Rabin confirmed the decision, stating there was insufficient evidence to challenge the contamination claim.
title: Chinese swimmers to compete at Olympics despite +ve doping tests

description: Saudi Arabia's ambitious plans extend beyond AlUla, with Neom being another significant project in the kingdom's northwestern region. Futuristic enclave is designed to attract a substantial number of newcomers to live and work in the area. Plans for Neom include a 100-mile-long city known as the Line, an octagon-shaped floating industrial complex, and an outdoor ski resort featuring artificial snow.
title: Why Saudi Arabia is making a high-risk $1 trillion bet on tourism
'Bishnoi gang to carry major incident in Mumbai': Cops

description: An overnight 'bombing' at the Calso military base in Babylon province, causing injuries to multiple individuals. The incident involved one death and eight injuries, with three Iraqi military personnel wounded. Hashed al-Shaabi confirmed the explosion, leading to 'material losses' and casualties. The responsible party and the use of drones remain unverified.
title: 'Bombing' hits Iraq military base, 1 killed

description: Most Gujaratis strive for commercial success, but Agriculture Produce Marketing Committee of Surat took it a step farther by building a mall and a five-star hotel on land acquired by the Gujarat government in the 1960s for the benefit of farmers. SC bench of Chandrachud and J B Pardiwala castigated Surat APMC for frittering away land meant for welfare of farmers.
title: APMC constructing a mall and five-star hotel is a scam: SC

description: When Mahendra Singh Dhoni steps up to bat, fans anticipate an electrifying performance from the legendary cricketer. In the ongoing IPL 2024 season, Dhoni has been in exceptional form, maintaining a strike rate of 255.88. Despite his excellent form and high run-rate acceleration, the question remains: Why is Dhoni not batting higher up in the order?
title: Why is MS Dhoni not batting up the order for CSK?

description: Missile defense is technically complex and expensive. It's almost like firing a bullet to deflect an incoming bullet. However, with the sheer operational criticality of air and missile defence systems reinforced by Israel and Iran's tit-for-tat attacks, India must significantly ramp up efforts to make its airspace as impenetrable as possible.
title: Israel-Iran attacks show India needs greater thrust on multi-layered air, missile def systems

description: Charu Asopa, who returned to TV after nearly three years of maternity break, decided to quit the show. She says she will now focus on web series, weekend shows, and social media content.
title: Exclusive - Charu Asopa on quitting Kaisa Hai Yeh Rishta Anjana
Elon Musk postpones India trip due to 'heavy Tesla obligations'

description: Jharsuguda boat incident death toll hits five as ferry capsizes in Mahanadi river. Passengers from Chhattisgarh were visiting Patharseni temple. Odisha announces Rs 4 lakh ex gratia. Ongoing rescue for missing.
title: Odisha boat tragedy: Death toll rises to five, rescue ops under way

description: In a heartwarming moment at an airport, Mumbai Indians' captain Hardik Pandya played with little Advik, son of Piyush Chawla. A video shared on social media captured Pandya tossing a ball to Advik, turning waiting time into a training session. Mumbai Indians have found their winning rhythm in the IPL, led by stellar performances by players like Suryakumar Yadav.
title: Watch: Hardik Pandya babysits Piyush Chawla's son at airport

description: Banmeet Singh, a 40-year-old Indian national, has been sentenced to five years in prison for selling controlled substances on dark web marketplaces. He was ordered to forfeit approximately USD 150 million. Singh created vendor marketing sites on dark web marketplaces like Silk Road, Alpha Bay, Hansa, and others, selling substances including fentanyl, LSD, ecstasy, Xanax, ketamine, and tramadol.
title: Indian sentenced for 5 yrs for selling controlled substance on dark web

description: Running is crucial for fitness but risky for joints. Overstriding, poor technique, and ignoring pain can lead to injuries like ankle sprain. Proper form, footwear, and warm-ups are vital for joint health and prevention of injuries.
title: Running mistakes that weaken your joints

description: As Dhoni made his way to the dressing room following his cameo in the IPL match between Chennai Super Kings and Mumbai Indians at Mumbai's Wankhede Stadium, he halted on the stairs at the sight of young Meher and her father. Pausing, he retrieved the ball from the steps and kindly presented it to her.
title: Watch: After gift from Dhoni, little girl makes a promise

description: After the India-Bangladesh land-swapping agreement, Dinhata residents gained citizenship through an EPIC card, transforming their lives with improved access to facilities and job opportunities. However, concerns persist over unmet promises despite the relocation.
title: Now proud Indians, ex-enclave dwellers thrilled to get inked

description: The upcoming elections hold immense significance for HD Deve Gowda, BS Yediyurappa, and DK Shivakumar. Shivakumar's ability to navigate the challenges and sustain his political momentum will determine the outcome, potentially reshaping the Congress party's trajectory nationally.
title: Can DKS turn Cong’s grip over Vokkaliga heartland into stranglehold?

description: The BCCI has fined Lucknow Super Giants and Chennai Super Kings for slow over-rate during their IPL match. KL Rahul and Ruturaj Gaikwad, the captains of both teams, have each been penalized with INR 12 Lakh. They were fined for their teams' slow over-rate during Match 34 of the Indian Premier League 2024 against Chennai Super Kings.
title: IPL: BCCI fines Rahul and Gaikwad Rs 12 lakh each
Why Quinton de Kock's wife shared 'Apple Watch warning'

description: Gottipati Lakshmi, a TDP candidate from Darsi, demonstrated her commitment to medical duty over politics by performing a life-saving C-section during her election campaign. Her swift action in handling a critical case showcases her dedication to healthcare.
title: Doctor-turned-neta puts duty over politics, ensures safe delivery

description: The much-awaited Bitcoin software upgrade, known as the "halving," has been successfully implemented, potentially impacting the profitability of companies that ensure the smooth and secure operation of the digital currency. This event, which occurs every four years, reduced the "mining reward" by half. According to data from analytics website mempool.space and Blockchain.com, the modification took effect at 8:10pm New York time on Friday evening. Following the halving, the price of Bitcoin remained relatively stable, hovering around $64,000.
title: Bitcoin ‘halving’ cuts supply of new tokens in threat to miners

description: AAP rebels refuse to withdraw from MCD deputy mayor election, criticizing party democracy. BJP anticipates AAP disintegration due to internal issues. Congress support to AAP noted. Potential impact on election results discussed as AAP faces challenges after Arvind Kejriwal's arrest.
title: MCD deputy mayor poll: AAP has a rebel problem

description: CPM in Kerala aims to improve its performance by focusing on minority votes, fielding heavyweights, and opposing CAA. The party's strategies include counting votes under its symbol and emphasizing its role at the national level.
title: Lok Sabha elections: Why CPM is fancying its chances in Kerala
